 Cape St Francis Bay, East London, Port Elizabeth and Port Alfred seem to have received much of the rain that fell on the Eastern and Southern Cape overnight. According to the Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service, 72mm of rain fell in Cape St Francis Bay while rain measuring above 31mm was recorded in East London while good rains were recorded at 3rd Avenue Dip, Flower Reserve, Riverstone Bridge, St Albans and at the airport in Port Elizabeth. Mar-18 Station Names 16 Nelson Mandela Bay  AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 20.2 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 27.6 ARS Blue Horizon Bay * AWSH Chatty 10.0 AWS Coega 13.8 AWSH Fettes Road 19.4 ARS Flower Reserve 33.0 ARS Lovemore Heights * AWSH Motherwell 13.0 ARS Riverstone Bridge 27.2 ARS St Albans 21.0 AWS Uitenhage 6.2    Catchment  AWS Joubertina 2.2 Man Kareedouw 4.0 Man Kouga Dam * AWS Patensie 13.2 Man Swartkops  17.1 Man   Other Towns  AWS Addo 6.2 AWS Bisho/KWT 12.2 AWS Cape St Francis 73.6 AWS Cradock 1.6 AWS East London 31.2 AWS Fort Beaufort 10.6 AWS George 18.5 AWS Graaff Reinet Nil AWS Grahamstown 14.6 AWS Henry`s Flats 5.2 AWS Joubertina 2.2 AWS Mossel Bay 5.4 AWS Mthatha 22.6 AWS Plettenberg bay 14.4 AWS Port Alfred 24.2 AWS Queenstown 1.8 